timelineItems.name: Corbin Cannon
timelineItems.text: Great rivalry day today! First #TOTvARS now #HOUvSKC! Go @SportingKC!

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: Leo showing a bit of hustle out there. Hope it means he wants to stick around long term. #TheFutureIsOrange #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Christian Montano
timelineItems.text: Game time!!! #dynamo (@ BBVA Compass Stadium - @bbvacompassstdm in Houston, TX) https://t.co/rhsE0PnolY http://t.co/DI68eOsjoJ

timelineItems.name: Nathan Martin
timelineItems.text: De Jong protecting Feilhaber & Nagamura protecting Zusi has shown signs of KC playing whole width on road as opposed to a side. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Troy Diggs
timelineItems.text: Jake and Nate keep talking about this match getting physical. When does Dom put on the Olivia Newton-John tights and leg warmers? #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: Will Bruin isn't a lone striker. It makes it al.ost impossible for him to succeed. #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Greg Boege
timelineItems.text: Way to stay standing until you reach the penalty box and then fall down, Bruin. #SportingKC

timelineItems.name: Tom Benton
timelineItems.text: My wife advises me that she still has negative feelings toward Brad Davis. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: The Houston Dynamo and Sporting Kansas City renew their rivalry with playoff implications.

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 90+3' Besler hammers a long ball downfield. Dwyer manages to redirect it on goal but it's into the hands of Deric. 1-0 #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: FT: @HoustonDynamo grab crucial 1-0 win vs. @SportingKC: http://t.co/UFSs0Xthpk #HOUvSKC http://t.co/hfqVg0a6GM

timelineItems.desc: The Houston Dynamo and Sporting Kansas City renew their rivalry with playoff implications.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Houston Dynamo vs. Sporting Kansas City | September 23, 2015

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 20' Olabiyi scampers forward and flashes in a low cross from the right flank. Matt Besler there to clear out of play. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Solid defense from DaMarcus Beasley, age 76. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Maddie Gregory
timelineItems.text: @HoustonDynamo @BBVACompassStdm Here with friends is always better than working the game! #ForeverOrange Go Dynamo⚽️ http://t.co/NTE4TmDrxb

timelineItems.name: David A. Ruiz
timelineItems.text: If Barnes gets a yellow card he's gonna miss next match #houvskc #foreverorange

timelineItems.name: Jack Rowlands
timelineItems.text: I love Beasley. What a man. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 25' Feilhaber slips a delightful through ball into the path of Nagamura, but he's flagged off side. Man, that was close... #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Kenny Bacak
timelineItems.text: The beautiful game. #mls #dynamo. http://t.co/PMmc9ngLcK

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: Oscar at RB....I know he can do the job on paper but.... #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 3' Marcel de Jong gets on the end of Zusi's set piece, but his header from the corner of the six-yard box is high and wide. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Bryan Hernandez
timelineItems.text: I've completely lost faith in Miranda #HOUvSKC #ForeverOrange

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: I was going to say that's a yellow for Sinovic, but if Barnes didn't get a yellow, neither should Seth. Yay for consistency. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Andrew Wiebe
timelineItems.text: Sporting KC and Houston doing what Sporting KC and Houston do on a Wednesday night. Put me right to sleep. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Soni Mustivar (Sporting Kansas City) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Soni Mustivar earns a yellow after taking down Will Bruin

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: First yellow goes to SKC for a bad tackle on Bruin. San Zusi been bad. #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Martin Hajovsky
timelineItems.text: Is there anything less threatening these days than a @HoustonDynamo set piece? How things have changed #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Taylor Twellman
timelineItems.text: The referee in #HOUvSKC just played advantage on a foul that was really really close to a penalty. Huh?!

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Zusi with too much club for that shot out of the rough. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Matt Besler (Sporting Kansas City) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Matt Besler sees yellow for his foul on Brad Davis

timelineItems.name: Scotty Toddy
timelineItems.text: All the attacking of Sunday night but with an opponent willing to play along! #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Kishan Patel
timelineItems.text: #Dynamo not using the wings either would help create more space and opportunities.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Giles Barnes (Houston Dynamo) right footed shot from outside the box is too high.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Giles Barnes sends a long-range effort over the bar

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: And with that, we're missing arguably our most important player for the next match against the red hot Sounders. ...GREAT. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Boniek Garcia (Houston Dynamo) is shown the yellow card.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Boniek Garcia cautioned for an elbow on Dom Dwyer

timelineItems.name: Bean
timelineItems.text: Olabiyi has a good touch, is two footed, and physically imposing, and moves around with ease. #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: Boniek flirted with danger. Danger flirted back. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: First half highlight: Deric falling asleep on the pitch from boredom and blocking a shot on the way down. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: HT: Not much happening in Houston. #HOUvSKC is 0-0: http://t.co/RqVejhC1Qq http://t.co/3OoOBOKq4L

timelineItems.name: Bryan Hernandez
timelineItems.text: This picture alone defines the match #HOUvSKC #ForeverOrange http://t.co/R39oaNb8VP

timelineItems.name: The Blue Testament
timelineItems.text: The second half is underway. Let’s see if SKC can get into the box more this half. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Encouraging sign early in the second half: Players are making faster moseys off the ball. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 47' Bruin is played through inside the box but Besler does very well to get his foot to it and clear. Zusi subesquently fouled. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Houston Dynamo
timelineItems.text: 50' Long throw from Besler is flicked on by Myers, but Bruin heads it out for a corner at the back post. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Two really unremarkable corner kicks by Graham Zusi. Anyone got an idea on why he's been in a funk for a year? #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Attempt blocked. Ricardo Clark (Houston Dynamo) left footed shot from the center of the box is blocked.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Tim Melia is finally tested by Ricardo Clark

timelineItems.name: Kishan Patel
timelineItems.text: Brilliant counterattack from the #Dynamo

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: Don't think Melia would have gotten that if Ellis wasn't there. He was going one way and the ball the other. Good work from Ellis. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Seth Sinovic (Sporting Kansas City) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Seth Sinovic goes into the book

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Small flurry of activity from both teams: Anomaly or sign of better things to come? #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Jesse Gilmore
timelineItems.text: WHY! WHY PETERSON! He can't score unless we're playing Toronto! #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: Great hustle from Bruin but his cross is long to Leo and poor Miranda is cleaned out by Sinovic. Yellow. #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Houston Dynamo
timelineItems.text: 58' Barnes is walking off gingerly but under his own power, we'll see if he can continue. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: And Cubo makes the jog from warmups and looks like he'll get a half hour tonight. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Oh, man ... that's rough. Somewhere in Chile, Luis Marin has just conceded a goal to the Dynamo. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Deporte Total USA
timelineItems.text: Ya se juega #HOUvSKC aquí en el @BBVACompassStdm http://t.co/KQs6JalGLs

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 4' Horst topples Feihaber from behind and it's another free kick for the visitors, this one from near the center circle. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Houston Dynamo
timelineItems.text: 60' Davis with a left-footed shot from 25 yards or so because why not, but it skips right into Melia's hands. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Miranda with a little sombrero over Nagamura and the Dynamo unleash a counter... until... it goes nowhere. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Brad Davis left footed shot from the center of the box is saved by Tim Melia.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Tim Melia makes a great stop on Brad Davis

timelineItems.name: Michael Sanchez
timelineItems.text: This is some of the worst attacking I've seen from the #Dynamo in a long time. They need to figure this out before end of season

timelineItems.name: Michael Sanchez
timelineItems.text: Losing guys mid season for Gold Cup hurt and could tell Coyle didn't know how to handle it like Dom #Dynamo

timelineItems.desc: Goal! Houston Dynamo 1, Sporting Kansas City 0. Will Bruin (Houston Dynamo) right footed shot from very close range to the bottom right corner. Assisted by DaMarcus Beasley.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Will Bruin opens the scoring for Houston

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 62' TIM MELIA, LADIES AND GENTS! Incisive attack from Houston as Clark squares it to Barnes, but @TimMelia28 makes the reflex save! #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: 67' GOAL for Houston. DaMarcus Beasley does Bad Man things down the wing and Bruin toe pokes in for this 11th of the year #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Brian Sciaretta
timelineItems.text: It's been a great 2 days for #usmnt players abroad. Beasley makes his mark on the domestic side - nice work for the assist to Bruin #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.desc: Second yellow card to Boniek Garcia (Houston Dynamo) for another foul on Dom Dwyer (Sporting KC).
timelineItems.title: RED CARD: Boniek Garcia receives a second yellow

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 6' Feilhaber spreads it wide to Zusi who serves a bouncing cross into the middle from the right wing, but Boniek Garcia intercepts. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Giles hits the bench and has his head in hands while medical staff go to work on him. Rough night for the Jamaican International #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Red Card to Boniek Garcia for what appeared to be a flung elbow to Dwyer's face. On replay, looked incidential #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Daniel
timelineItems.text: Orange smoke engulfs the stadium after Dynamo goal. #HTX #Houston #Dynamo http://t.co/jjHWyDBep8

timelineItems.name: Tom Benton
timelineItems.text: Dom Dwyer is a pest, but opponents still aren't allowed to beat him about the head. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: BÃ¶yce
timelineItems.text: Even up a man, SKC still will not win this match, b/c Kevin Ellis will manage to give up another goal. #sportingkc

timelineItems.name: Cody Hink
timelineItems.text: #sportingkc really needs to figure out their backline. Just a mess.

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 76' #SportingKC settling into a period of dominant possession as Houston is playing down a man due to Boniek Garcia's ejection. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Matt Pollard
timelineItems.text: Sporting just looks burned out. Zusi hasn't been himself since the World Cup (though, that's not completely his fault). #SportingKC #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Generation Orange
timelineItems.text: This is a good sign: Oscar and Brad way off on a simple restart. Waste offensive chance and turn ball over... #ForeverOrange #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: sparksjay
timelineItems.text: #SKC couldn't mount a taxidermy project, much less an attack in this match.

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Owen Coyle giving instruction to Beasley on the sideline. Trying to get the team to focus for the last ten minutes #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 83' Excellent diagonal ball from Quintilla to Sinovic, whose cross to the far post is headed wide by a leaping Nagamura. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Should have waited for the Mattapult there. Going to take something like that for Sporting to bunker-bust, I think. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Cody Hink
timelineItems.text: Down a goal with less than 10 min, let's have our back line play kick back #sportingkc

timelineItems.desc: Benny Feilhaber (Sporting Kansas City) is shown the yellow card.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Benny Feilhaber gets a yellow card

timelineItems.name: SKC Gameday
timelineItems.text: 88' SKC looking for a way through, but Houston has dropped deep and remained organized since going up 1-0. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Tom Benton
timelineItems.text: What in the world is Benny thinking there? #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Richard Fleming
timelineItems.text: Sporting KC not using their heads with the man advantage. #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Dynamo with a terrific counter that starts from a Raul clearance. Alex's ball across is poor, however, and the chance is gone #HOUvSKC

timelineItems.name: Deporte Total USA
timelineItems.text: Todo listo ! #HOUvSKC http://t.co/jRK8qW7lVa

timelineItems.name: Chris George
timelineItems.text: Game in hand goes away tonight. Better be traded for 3 points. #sportingkc

timelineItems.name: Justin Jerkins
timelineItems.text: Oh hey Donatas Motiejunas sighting. This has to be his fourth or fifth game this season. #ForeverOrange
